data.title: Visits by Foreign Leaders
data.text: Prime Minister Fraser Guest of the President. Attended a Pacific War Council meeting. August 26–September 4, 1942 Prime Minister Fraser En route to London for conference of British Commonwealth Prime Ministers. Attended opening session of the International Labor Organization in Philadelphia (Pennsylvania), April 20. Afterwards visited New York City. April 14–22, 1944 Prime Minister Fraser Led New Zealand delegation to the United Nations Conference in San Francisco. April 25–June 26, 1945 Prime Minister Holland Met with President Truman February 8 while returning from a Commonwealth conference in London. February 5–10, 1951 Prime Minister Holland Met with President Eisenhower en route to London for the coronation of Queen Elizabeth II. May 17–20, 1953 Prime Minister Holland Unofficial visit. Left New York City January 27. January 20–23, 1955 Prime Minister Holyoake Informal visit; discussed Laos crisis with President Kennedy. In U.S. March 2–4. March 3, 1961 Prime Minister Holyoake Informal visit while attending UN General Assembly. September 27–28, 1962 Prime Minister Holyoake Attended ANZUS Council meeting. July 17–20, 1964 Prime Minister Keith J. Holyoake Official visit. In U.S. October 6–16; attended ANZUS Council meeting and visited Los Angeles, New York City, and Seattle. October 9–10, 1968 Prime Minister Keith J. Holyoake Official visit. In U.S. September 14–21; visited Los Angeles and New York City. September 15–18, 1969 Prime Minister Keith J. Holyoake Informal visit. April 8, 1971 Prime Minister Norman E. Kirk Official visit; fifth to the U.S.; first as Head of Government. September 26–29, 1973 Prime Minister Wallace E. Rowling Private visit. May 7, 1975 Prime Minister Robert D. Muldoon Official visit. Private visit afterwards to LaGrange (Ga.). November 8–11, 1977 Prime Minister Robert D. Muldoon Private visit. September 28, 1978 Prime Minister Robert D. Muldoon Private visit. Opened new Chancery. September 18–20, 1979 Prime Minister Robert D. Muldoon Private visit. Met with President Reagan July 24; visited New York City. July 23–25, 1981 Prime Minister Robert D. Muldoon Official working visit. February 22–25, 1984 Prime Minister James Bolger Met with President Clinton during a private visit. March 25–29, 1995 Prime Minister Jenny Shipley Private visit; attended Global Forum on Reinventing Government. February 13–15, 1999 Prime Minister Helen Clark Working visit. March 20–21, 2007 Prime Minister John Key Attended the Nuclear Security Summit. April 12–13, 2010 Prime Minister John Key Working visit. July 22, 2011
